   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The smart slot translator converts the RS-232 signals from the
Silcon protocol to the Smart Link protocol. The connection from the
communication interface is to a RS-232 port with a DE-9 connector
(male), using the Silcon protocol. The two-way connections to the
NMC and the options slots are from RS-232 ports with 10 pin IDC-connectors,
using the Smart Link protocol.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The smart slot translator has a serial monitoring port, a RS-232
port with a DE-9 connector (female). With a serial cable it is possible
to access the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Command Line Interface (CLI)</b> from this port.</p>
